---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../config/site';
import { webPageJsonLd } from '../lib/seo';

const title = 'Privacy Policy — FreeIQCheck';
const description = `Privacy Policy for ${site.domain}. Learn how we collect, use, and protect data including cookies, Google Analytics, and advertising.`;
---

<LegalLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  path="/privacy-policy"
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  jsonLd={[webPageJsonLd(title, description, '/privacy-policy')]}
>
  <p>
    FreeIQCheck (&quot;we,&quot; &quot;us,&quot; or &quot;our&quot;) operates <a href={site.url}>{site.url}</a>, a free online IQ-style
    reasoning quiz and educational website. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard information when
    you visit our site.
  </p>
  <p>
    By using FreeIQCheck, you agree to the practices described here. If you do not agree, please discontinue use of the website.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <h3>Information you provide</h3>
  <p>
    We do not require an account to take our quiz. If you contact us by email, we receive the information you choose to send (such as your
    email address and message content) solely to respond to your inquiry.
  </p>
  <h3>Quiz and browser data</h3>
  <p>
    The IQ quiz runs primarily in your browser. Answer selections may be stored temporarily in <strong>session storage</strong> on your
    device to display results on the results page. Theme preference (light/dark mode) may be stored in <strong>local storage</strong>.
    You can clear this data anytime through your browser settings.
  </p>
  <h3>Automatically collected information</h3>
  <p>
    Like most websites, we and our service providers may automatically collect certain technical information, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>IP address (often truncated or anonymized where supported)</li>
    <li>Browser type, device type, and operating system</li>
    <li>Pages viewed, referring URLs, and approximate geographic region</li>
    <li>Date, time, and duration of visits</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Our hosting provider (e.g., Cloudflare Pages) may process server logs for security, performance, and reliability.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <p>We use collected information to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Operate, maintain, and improve the website and quiz experience</li>
    <li>Understand aggregate traffic and usage patterns through analytics</li>
    <li>Display advertisements (where enabled) and measure ad performance</li>
    <li>Detect, prevent, and address technical issues or abuse</li>
    <li>Respond to contact requests and legal obligations</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information to third parties.</p>

  <h2>Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files stored on your device. We and our partners use cookies and similar technologies for essential site
    functions, analytics, and advertising.
  </p>
  <h3>Types of cookies we may use</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential / functional:</strong> theme preference and quiz session data stored locally</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> to understand how visitors use our site (see Google Analytics below)</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> to serve and measure ads, including through Google AdSense and its partners</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You can control cookies through your browser settings. Blocking cookies may affect site functionality. To opt out of personalized
    advertising from Google, visit <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>.
    For industry opt-out tools, see <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">aboutads.info</a> (US) or
    <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Your Online Choices</a> (EU).
  </p>

  <h2>Google Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> (measurement ID: {site.gaMeasurementId}) to collect aggregated usage statistics. Google
    Analytics uses cookies and may collect information such as how often users visit pages, what pages were viewed, and what other sites
    were used prior to visiting. We use this data to improve content and user experience.
  </p>
  <p>
    Google&apos;s ability to use and share information collected by Analytics is governed by the
    <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a>. You may opt out
    using the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>
    or your browser&apos;s privacy controls.
  </p>

  <h2>Google AdSense and advertising partners</h2>
  <p>
    We may display advertisements served by <strong>Google AdSense</strong> and other third-party ad vendors. These partners may use
    cookies, web beacons, and similar technologies to serve ads based on your visits to this and other websites, and to measure ad
    effectiveness.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on a user&apos;s prior visits to our website or other
      websites.
    </li>
    <li>
      Google&apos;s use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to users based on their visit to our site
      and/or other sites on the Internet.
    </li>
    <li>
      Users may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
      <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    For more information about how Google uses data from partner sites, see
    <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">How Google uses information from sites or apps that use our services</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Ad partners are independent controllers of data they collect. We encourage you to review their privacy policies. We do not control
    third-party ad content or tracking practices.
  </p>

  <h2>Legal bases (EEA/UK visitors)</h2>
  <p>
    Where applicable, we process personal data based on: (a) your consent (e.g., non-essential cookies where required); (b) legitimate
    interests in operating and improving our site; and (c) compliance with legal obligations.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    Server logs and analytics data are retained only as long as necessary for the purposes described above, typically in aggregated or
    anonymized form. Email correspondence is retained as needed to resolve inquiries. Local quiz data remains on your device until you
    clear browser storage.
  </p>

  <h2>Children&apos;s privacy</h2>
  <p>
    FreeIQCheck is intended for a general audience. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 (or the
    applicable age in your jurisdiction) without parental consent. If you believe a child has provided personal information, contact us
    and we will take reasonable steps to delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>International visitors</h2>
  <p>
    If you access the site from outside the United States, your information may be processed in countries where our service providers
    operate, which may have different data protection laws than your country.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict processing of personal data, or to object
    to certain processing. To exercise rights, email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>. We will respond within a
    reasonable timeframe as required by law.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The &quot;Last updated&quot; date at the top will reflect revisions. Material
    changes may be noted on this page. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Privacy questions: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> · <a href="/contact">Contact form page</a>
  </p>
  <p>
    See also our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> and <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
